< Review>
So glad I found this cafe in downtown Covina. My order was ready in about 15 minutes and due to covid, they brought it out to my car. I ordered the kids pancakes, kids french toast and a protein sandwich...all were amazing! My kids are picky eaters and loved every bite. The fruit was fresh and food was flavorful and well portioned. Yours and Mine is one of the brightest spots in the Eastern SGV‚Äôs breakfast choices. While their youth as a restaurant can lead to longer waits, the menu more than makes up for this sure-to-be-improved challenge. From the fluffiest pancakes in town, to the excellent scrambles and the fine lunch options, Yours and Mine has scrumptious food that tastes fresh and inviting. <text>I really wanted to give this place a chance, I really did. The menu seemed interesting, the atmosphere was cozy, and I wanted to support our local small businesses. So we get there (party of four) and the one girl working (hostess/waitress/busser) told us she just needed to clear the tables and we'd get seated right away. I glance around and there is maybe three small families waiting/ sitting at their tables with unhappy faces (should of been a red flag) and I see there are five other EMPTY tables that just need to get plates picked up and wiped down. Okay I think, five minutes top.

FORTY minutes later we finally get seated, I honestly don't know why we hadn't left. But we are troopers and we continue to wait. Three other parties got seated at the same time we did, even though they arrived after us. Next, we are still waiting and ten more minutes and we get our menus. Waitress girl is all over the place, giving menu, taking orders,  serving drinks all out of order. Some one came in to order to go and left happily with their food. We moved from Denver, CO to Sydney Australia in Sept 2020. Mark Neville was unresponsive when the packers came to pack our house in 1 day instead of 2. They packed, food, medication and anything that wasn't nailed down. Because we sold our house and were moving overseas, we could not reschedule.

Once we finally got our boxes and furniture in Sydney, furniture was damaged, a large part of my dishes and glasses were all broken, items were bent. The packaging was incompetence and damage was due to their negligence.
We were suppose to have an entire container and we are missing a part of our sectional sofa, 1 box of kitchen items and things from random boxes were missing and incorrectly labeled.
Shumachers response was pathetic - they don't care.
I would never recommend this company !</review>

<rating>1</rating><text>I've worked with Schumacher twice on our shipping container move over to Denmark and back.
The first time, moving to Denmark, there were a few off things, mostly about keeping us on the loop, informing us of the milestones, delays, etc., Especially bad was the performance of their subsidiary in Germany to deliver our furniture after being stalled for 4 weeks in Hamburg. They refused to deliver in Christmas so we had no furniture for one week. Schumacher did not manage their German 3rd party.
On our way back, we decided to give feedback to Schumacher about the previous experience and work again with them, to simplify things and hoping that the feedback would improve the experience. It got worse. Our container left Denmark on Nov-11th and stayed sitting in a warehouse in Hamburg until Christmas. When I followed up, they said they would try to put it on a vessel on Jan-8th. After that, we were unlucky to be inspected by German customs (not Schumacher fault). When they finally put our container on Jan-27, we learned that a vessel departs every Monday towards the Americas.
The ordeal did not end there, the vessel has arrived on Feb-20th (12 weeks later, when they commit to deliver door to door between 8 and 10 weeks) and now they've sent us a $3k custom inspection invoice with a one liner description that says: Inspection.
Not only haven't we been informed or cared for during the whole process but on top of the extra costs this is involving for us in additional Airbnb + rental furniture expenses, now they send us a $3K bill without explanation, context of justification. They really have no shame.

I would work with someone else if you're going to ship your stuff overseas. I made the mistake twice< /text>< Pictures>

< Text>
We used Schumacher in November 2019 to move some items from NY to Ireland. It was a sort of test run because we planned to move the bulk of our home to Ireland eventually. The few items  (including a cast iron and enamel sink) made it intact and within the timeline we were given.
The pandemic hit and we put our NYC home on the market. It sold, so we called Schumacher again and scheduled a move for September 2020. This time it was the full contents of our house, including loads of art and an upright piano.
The salesman, Chris Licalsi, did a virtual walkthrough and gave us an estimate which included adding our storage space to the total. The price was fair and within the market rate, so we decided to go with them based on our previous positive experience. Chris was totally honest and transparent both times we used Schumacher. His affable manner and patience was  assuring.
The movers were scheduled to take 4 days to pack and load our home and our storage locker. The crew, Charles M, Luis D, Lito H, and Joseph K were exceptional. They packed our possessions with great care, crated the piano and a glass table top, repacked most of the contents of our storage container in order to make them more secure for sea travel. Finally, they loaded the shipment onto the overseas container, closed up the container and we took photos of the secured  shipment and the numbered lock. We received the detailed inventory list as a pdf, and the timetable for arrival in Ireland was set. The container arrived on time with no hassle.
The receiving moving company in Ireland were equally helpful. They handled the paperwork and customs and walked us through the process. The dispatcher sent a crew of eight men and two shuttle vans. Our house is in the countryside and a shipping container would never get close to the house. The container was unloaded within three hours and all furniture placed and reassembled.
We were able to completely unpack within a month of arrival and not a single item was damaged or lost.
I highly recommend Schumacher for any overseas household moves.</Text>

< review>
I contracted Schumacher Cargo Logistics to ship my household effects (about 260 cubic feet) from San Jose, CA to Brisbane, Australia. They did a first class job from pickup at my apartment in San Jose to delivery to my storage cube in Brisbane.

Communication was excellent throughout (thank you Kimberly) and all my goods arrived safe and sound.

What you want when shipping your valuables overseas is a firm you can absolutely trust, because it will take a long time and there can be a significant variation between estimates and actual duration. It's a complicated procedure dealing with container ships from one side of the world to the other.

In my case, US customs decided to open the shared container which added a couple of weeks and resulted in an extra charge. This is stated on the contract, so be aware that it may happen to you.

You may find cheaper quotes out there, but check to see what they offer. The service Schumacher offers ($16 per cubic foot) is a full, door to door service.

It may seem a bit expensive but it is a very reliable service and they treat your valued possessions with care. At the end of the day, you want a shipper you can trust; the actual dollars are secondary.

I highly recommend Schumacher Cargo Logistics.

Regards,
Geoff</review>

<review>I had some large items which needed to be freighted from the USA to the Middle East.  Not being from the States and not knowing any US freight forwarders, it was a quick internet search, an email, and then a massive hope that things would go well.

It took a long time (2.5 months) for my shipment to travel from Texas to Italy because it was a relatively small one (ca. 20 boxes), but this was part of the deal and the reason why I was able to take advantage of their convenient rate for a shipment within 100 CFU and spend less money than paying for a 'regular' cargo on my own. In any case the price was worth the service. Schumacher Cargo Logistics staff was prompt not only in answering my questions but also in dealing with small glitches along the way. They allowed me to deliver some additional boxes to their warehouse after the main shipment was already there and reassemble it in order not to exceed the 100 CFU we agreed upon (and the related price). They helped me significantly with the paperwork required by European customs. They also covered some additional fees their European associated partner claimed after the shipment arrived in Rotterdam.
In conclusion, I strongly recommend their services to anyone moving from US to Europe.</Review>

<pics>None<//pics>< text>
We used Schumacher for a move from Texas to Scotland. They were a bit pricier than the other quotes I got but they had good reviews and did a full service type move. I felt that it was worth paying a bit more for a company I had more trust in.

The pick up in Texas went very well. The crew was professional and did an excellent job packing everything, even though we did a lot of it for them by pre-packing our items into plastic bins. In the end, only 1 small item was broken and 2 things turned up bent.

It took awhile to get our things from Texas to port in New York; almost a month, which seemed slow to me.

To get them out to sea and into port in London was a reasonable 2 weeks. And then clearing customs took another 10 days, which was also reasonable.

However, getting the goods from London up to Scotland and then delivered to us took over 5 weeks. This was pretty absurd for such a small country as the UK. And we actually contacted the company ourselves after such a long time, they didn't call us first.

After all of that, I still would have reviewed Schumacher well. However, the 1 notable piece of furniture that we actually shipped over, a large office desk, was left in pieces upon delivery. The delivery team couldn't figure out how to reassemble it . Thus they gave up and just left us with all of the pieces.

I contacted everyone involved on the sales and management side and they agreed to have the delivery team come back out to assemble it. However, it's been a month since that was coordinated and they still haven't arranged me to take care of it.

I couldn't go any longer without a working home office so I had to spend my weekend figuring out how to put the desk back together. That's not what I paid several thousand dollars for.< /text>

Our company does not inflate or exaggerate these costs, and we provide everyone who is selected by examinations with their invoice from the CBP Centralized Examination Station. 1542371677250<//date>
<Text>Stay away from Schumacher Cargo. I've never felt so deceived in my entire life.

I just moved back home and had to ship my car from California to Spain. I was given a quote for $1520 and paid in full when I dropped off my car with Schumacher Cargo. After TWO MONTHS of waiting for it to sail, they let me know that the container was halted by US Customs and want me to pay an EXTRA CHARGE of $743 or else they won't release my car.
I was NEVER told about US Customs inspections and had I known they were so expensive, I would have never shipped my car.
I stressed the need of going with the cheaper shipping method to my sales rep Kevin Lucarelli since I was on a very tight budget, and he never warned me about any such possible fees. I'm not shipping a Ferrari, it's actually a $13K car for which I'll have to pay total fees close to $3000.

Communication has been very difficult. Many of my emails were ignored and had to resend times and times over. If I asked 4 questions, I got 1 answered
Worst part is that out of all the shipping companies I talked to, they seemed to be the most trustful.

I feel completely scammed and ignored by Schumacher Cargo.

Here are the hidden fees I've come across:
- $75 for processing insurance documents
- $743 for customs exams (their fault, since they are the ones preparing the shipment and did something wrong that caused the container to get flagged for inspection)
- 4% of any invoice for paying with a credit card (ridiculous fees for a company operating internationally in 2018)
All these should be part of their business costs, and not something that honest customers who are going through the stressful process of moving overseas had to deal with.

Original review text:
If there were negative reviews available, Schumacher would have them all. I have done many moves in my life, both national and international but have never come across such an incompetent and unethical group. I like many of you reading reviews, saw a good overall rating for the company and thought they could be trusted. Dig deeper and check out yelp, BBB and mover websites and you will see the horror stories.

Below is a summary of our grievances.

We hired Schumacher Cargo to do a full pack up, move, deliver and unpack from Seattle, Washington to Dublin, Ireland. What we received was very different from what we paid for. Our dispute centres around four major issues:

1. Services we paid for not provided/not provided in a professional manner
My wife had to ring Schumacher multiple times the first and last day of the packing because the movers did not show up and did not have enough resources to get the job done.

Fast forward to the move. The move was delayed two weeks because the paperwork was not filed correctly by Schumacher. This caused the financial costs listed above plus destroyed our Christmas holiday.

2. Damages for items delivered
As we have unpacked boxes ourselves we are finding many missing parts and pieces (as well as numerous damaged items.

Again because of the poor packing job, in total about 25 percent or $52,000 of items insured are damaged, missing parts or just plain missing.

3. House Damage
In Seattle, the timber floor was gouged as the movers dragged things across the foyer floor. In the Dublin house there were dings in walls and moulding, a cracked tile in the kitchen and marks all over the walls in the corridors and stairwells.

4. Additional Fees Because Schumacher Did not Provide the Proper Documentation to the Dublin Movers
Our goods were delayed over two weeks because Schumacher did not provide the local mover in Dublin with the proper import paperwork. This delayed the delivery and cost us an additional 165.00 EUR fee and 1,062 EUR in port charges.

In summary, for the $23,446.78 we paid Schumacher we did not get the service we paid for, over 2x this amount in damaged goods, damaged houses and additional import fees.</review>

<text>UNFORTUNATELY NO OPTION TO GIVE ZERO STARS

DO NOT USE THIS COMPANY! THEY WILL CONTINUE TO CHARGE AFTER ITEMS DELIVERED WITH MADE UP FEE'S

We paid to get our personal items shipped from the UK to USA with a British company Britannia Movers International who outsourced the US part to Schumacher Cargo Logistics in Los Angeles, 550 W 135th St, Gardena, CA 90248

Having already paid for the agreed service we were hit by customs charges in the US and were given an invoice to pay without the breakdown of the charges and how our portion was calculated. As they had our goods, we had to pay otherwise they would charge for daily storage.

Having settled the custom charges we were given a form to fill out for the delivery address and we stated on the form that there were between 40 -50 steps. On the day of delivery, the guys mentioned it will cost $150 for carrying the items up the steps, we told them we had declared on the form that there were steps and nothing more was said. They continued to carry our items up; we paid $40 in cash to the delivery guys for their work and they accepted this and did not mention we were short of $110. After they had left, we received an email with an invoice for $150. The delivery guys did not communicate with us as we would have told them that we will carry it up the steps ourselves.

We have tried to explain to Schumacher Cargo Logistics directly as this is an unfair charge. Their response was to refer to the form ‚Äòif additional fees for shuttle, stair carry, elevator or any other accessorial services to incur, the balance must be paid by customer no later than 7 days of delivery date. The balance can only be paid in cash on the day of delivery.‚Äô  on the same form we declared that we had between 40 -50 steps and not once was this mentioned that the cost for extra steps would be $5.36 per step after the 8 free steps (Also not mentioned on the form).  The way the form was worded suggests that if any of our information is wrong then there may be additional charges, NOT that they might decide to charge us what they feel like after we have already accepted delivery.

They have now threatened to send our invoice to collections if we don‚Äôt pay by end of tomorrow 8th Feb '19. Surely an invoice in dispute should be put on hold until a resolution has been made.</text><pics>None</pics>< resp>

< Review>
This was our second move with Schumacher (first from Tucson to Germany, and now back to Tucson). The service and communication were very clear and fast. We were told precisely, what the customs charges might be (the quotation lists that additional customs charges will arise and after calling them to ask, they clarified that the charges will be billed after customs clearance). There were no surprises with additional charges - everything was communicated and explained before we booked the shipment. We dropped off our belongings in LA and Houston ourselves to save some money and the warehouse crews were incredibly professional and friendly. To see the warehouses and the level of organization going on there put our minds at ease because we knew that our motorcycle and household goods were in good hands.
Schumacher was not the cheapest quote that we received- but its a company where there are no surprises or additional charges or delays - it was a worry free experience for us - well - just as worry free as an international move can be :)< /Review>

<date>1524051533593<//date><user>106979856319936208321</user><gmap_id>0x80c2ca6c29ff06c9:0x1f0f2b8571378b1f<//gmap_id><review>Before I go into all the details, please note that I have never seen a product or services that earned 5 Stars, until now.
I am an American that decided to move from Southern California to Romania. I moved sixty years of memories, belongings and my Harley Davidson to be with my extended family here.  The Move started in November of 2017,from two different locations there. The first to be loaded up was the house. Second was my storage unit which was fifteen miles from the house. Ergo, I was on the telephone and the Internet for what seemed like hours. Be prepared ! Seriously, this the one time that you must read the "small print ." I must say that I didn't at first. The prices will vary imensele. IE I found a company that half the costs of Schumacher ! However, the old saying that "you get what you pay for?" I found this to be absolutely true. My sales representative, Nathan Stowell certainly was upfront and honest through the entire process. His professionalism and experience definitely not go unmentioned. Nathan walked me through all of this small print mentioned. I will not go into why payment was very late, everyone has issues and/or problems with their financial institutions. Which brings me to the Accounts Receivable department there at Schumachers Gardena office. It's now April 2018 and payment has not arrived! Another true professional informed me substantial late and storage fees. Pamela Elliott even though I could not provide her with appropriate documentation as to why the payment was late , Pamela Elliott took me at my word and waived said fees!?! Honestly, my bank was guilty not Schumacher!  Folks we live in the greatest country on the planet the USA!  Most companies would have been sitting on all my belongings until Paid In Full and rightfully so! Not Schumacher!!! Quite frankly, I was and currently am still in awe. As the company had already shipped all of my memories and before receiving payment in full first? ! Remarkable!  As most know this just doesn't happen in America, period! I paid them immediately ! To trust in me? A person that they had never met face to face ? Yes I'm sure that they had recourse, if payment was not made. My point is that these professional people are in good, if not great people and they treated me as a person. In closing, if you want professional people like taking care of your items that are important to you and care about you ? Schumacher is the answer to your moving needs. What else can I say?  TRY THEM YOU'LL LIKE THEM!
Once again, I have NEVER given 5 Stars to any service or product before. Also I have never written such a long review! They merit both!

Most clients want the most competitive rate we can offer, which is in a shared container. This means we cannot guarantee the sail date until we have a full container to load.\n90% of our shipments leave with 2-4 weeks of drop off and then the sail time is variant, depending on the destination.\nWe ship 18,000 vehicles a year and sometimes, certain files are delayed for very specific reasons. Summary: Great shippers. 8-10 weeks from LA to Sydney, very responsive and timely communication. Always willing to keep customer happy.

We recently immigrated from LA (USA) to Sydney (Australia). Had many options for shipping, I was about to go with XYZ shipper, when I found Schumacher Cargo online and spoke to with Mark. Being Aussie himself he was knowledgeable with the customs and Quarantine process. That 1 phone call made me change my mind. I confirmed with SCL. They were not the least expensive, but were very competitive and provided door-to-door. Most of all, I felt like I was in good hands. Over time their assistance and responsiveness to my queries and requests confirmed that I was. The pick-up, packaging at my house was quick, professional.

Edwin next took up my case and followed up with updates on warehouse receipt, updated quote (which was close to my initial estimate). bill of lading, destination delivery company, ship details and when it docked in Sydney.

Pamela from the A/c Receivable was great to work with as well. There was a minor change I wanted made in my account summary. She helped me out pretty quick. Easy breezy!

From then on the local shipper has been in touch with me and I'm waiting for my goods now. I know it's been through quarantine (AQIS). It's probably finishing Customs now.<//review>

This was a fast and accurate shipment, you can see the timeline below as well. What you did not understand was the customs process and organization we had to put in place to safe guard the transition of your car from German customs, through to Polish customs. Your opinion on how we handled this is perspective, and not accurate to the reality of what had to happen, all to your benefit.\n\nAnyone reading this who has shipped cars overseas will know the timeline involved.\n\nEvery destination is different. Poland is not a popular destination for shared container service, this is why we routed your car via Germany, which is a very common entry port for a lot of EU countries. We offer a shared container service to over 80 destinations worldwide, which is the service you chose due to the competitive nature of the quote. The time frame is never guaranteed and you were aware of this from the start.\n\nWe did understand your frustration due to a delay, however that is part of consolidation and international logistics. It seems like nothing we did would have appeased you and to insinuate that we purposefully rerouted your shipment (which added additional "no charge" hours of coordination with overseas agents from our operations department, not to mention documentation filing) simply to charge you a few hundred dollars extra is just false.\n\nHi Schumacher,\nREF# HOU0033227\nI got the car and personal goods on 1st June and everything looks good. Thank you!\nThe last thing is the matter of additional costs I was forced into due to the lack of proper organization.\n* There was no lack of proper organization- this was an international shipment of a vehicle from Houston to Bremerhaven port in Germany, where it had to be customs cleared and then re directed legally to Poland where it needed to be customs cleared yet again, using a T1 import document. We did all this professionally and to the letter of the law.\nThe deal was to transport the car to Gdynia (Poland) by sea.\n* The deal was to ship your car from Houston to Poland- we did that. The fact that it was routed via Germany is a standard logistical process that we as your freight forwarder chose to expedite your shipment. Shared container service is what you chose, and this is part of that process.\nI understand that you have changed plans due to lack of containers to Gdynia that\'s okey with me.\n* Here you agree with the situation\nWhat I don\'t understand is the three additional costs that occurred on my side and should be covered by Schumacher.\n* The additional charges amounted to $200 to account for the transport of your car with an agent who could service the shipment in Germany\n* Plus some additional customs documents needed to cross the border\n* These were all explained to you at the time\n\nUnfortunately the length of our response is limited to a certain length, however we will be happy to discuss in more detail whenever you like.\n\nRegards,\n\nSchumacher Cargo'}<//resp>< Gmap_id>

<Review>Chicken was cooked properly so it tasted really fresh. There was some wait as expected..I pretty much enjoyed their Gochujang sauce (Korean style hot sauce for chicken) and I can tell the sauce has enhanced taste of Gochujang (thick soypaste mixed with red peppers). Generally, I think there are four kinds of Korean style sauces for chicken. 1. Soy sauce (relatively new). 2. Hot sauce (hot & sweet; sometimes, very mildly hot but extremely sweet). 3. Hot sauce (more with 'deep' Gochujang flavour). 4. Nothing (perhaps only with powdered salt as a side). Recently, I've been into the third version. So, it was really great here. However, the fried chicken itself was not like something that I can eat only in Korea.< /Review>< Pictures>

< Text>
I would give them zero star If I could. The worst customer service that I have ever received from a restaurant.

<text>Okay...let me start off with their terrible service. Even when there's hardly anyone there, they still can't provide decent service. When we arrived, our party of 5 sat down at the table that seats 6 people. When a party of 6 walked in, the woman came over and wanted us to move to a table for 4...which she would add a chair at the end of the table. Keep in mind that we've been seated for a while. She eventually figured out that if she puts 2 tables together, that works to seat 6 too! Through the course of our lunch, I must have walked up to the counter 4 times for water refills. Since there's no service, there shouldn't be a tipping option in their POS system.

I thought everything was pretty good, but felt a little gross after eating all of the greasy food. My personal favorite was the Gangnam Wings. A ton of flavor packed into these little things.

A lot of my Korean friends recommended this place to me so I had some high expectations but I didn't really see anything special about it. Service is meh, the girl who took our order just looked like she didn't want to be there. Their menu is pretty big and they have a lot of different types of chicken wing options. < Rate>

<Pictures>None<//Pictures>< text>
The first time I had this place I texted all my friend's with pics and RAVED about this place. It was by far the best wings I felt like I had ever had. You could smell the flavor through the bag!!! The fried wings (with 52 seasonings) were FIRE. But the soy garlic were  actually mouthwatering. I LOVE the pickled radish!!! The ranch dressing was flavorless but you truly don't need it for these wings. The next time I ordered, I was a little disappointed. I ordered the honey garlic wings and waffle fries. The wings were your typical run of the mill wings. Basic flavor, they were significantly smaller, and they had a thin skin...nothing like the soy garlic I previously had. What I loved about the first batch was the crunch! I'm down to try it again for sure, if it can get anywhere near the first time I tried it....I'm a fan for life!!!< /text>

102981016097599411146</user>
< resp>
None<//resp>
<text>BBQ Chicken is one of my all-time favorite spots to get Korean fried chicken in LA. They consistently provide quality food that makes me come running back for more.

Original Drumsticks: 5/5
This is my go-to item on the menu. I love the taste of the crispy, buttery skin with the tender, juicy meat. Their drumsticks also have a lot of meat on them, so having a few of them would probably satisfy your hunger. The original drumsticks have no flavor to them, but regardless they still taste amazing. You can purchase a sauce on the side and use it to dip the chicken, though it isn't necessary for me. I highly recommend, you can't go wrong with this choice!

BB Wings: 4/5
On their menu, they indicate the BB wings as spicy. However, I did not think they were spicy at all. The flavor was great nonetheless, but I thought they weren't worth it for its size. The wings are tiny and there isn't much meat on them. It honestly tasted like the mini version of the original drumstick, but with a bit of a kick to it.

Service: 1/5
I've never actually dined at this restaurant and I definitely would not want to, as their customer service is lacking. Every time I pick up my order, the servers are never friendly or welcoming. They also skimp out on the side dishes. For one order, they give you a free side dish of the radish. If you want an extra one, they make you pay an additional dollar. However, if I'm paying extra, I expect at least the same size of the free side dish. If you see my picture below, it's only one-third the size, which is pretty ridiculous. This is one of the few restaurants that I still go back to, despite the lack of customer service, because of the quality of their food.<//text><name>Regina Kempel<//name>< Gmap_id>

BBQ Chicken is one of the best fried chicken places in Ktown. Their chicken is so crispy and tasty especially their best seller dish, the half and half, that comes with half fried and half sweet spicy korean sauce. The place is small so there's not much seating available. Most people tend to order out here but I always choose to eat in as the restaurant has a relaxed setting and the lighting gives it a calm mood. Don't overlook this place the next time you're craving some delicious fried chicken in Ktown.<//Text>

< review>
How can I count the many ways chicken can be prepared.
I typically don't like to order chicken when I go out to eat because everyone is still scared of salmonella. I don't blame them for that but I do blame others for dry and overcooked chicken. With this place, they did what I like the most, dark meat. Chicken wings and drumsticks are dark meat so these were accompanied or slathered in sauce which makes for a better meal. Even the fried chicken legs are better than the Colonel. Better yet, BBQ Chicken should take the name of KFC. Korean Fried Chicken, done well. Just let me know when you want to work out on "leg day"!! I'll be your wing-man.< /review>

A different approach to fried chicken and man was it wonderfully delicious. I used to come here once every two weeks when I was in college. The service in passable, but the food is well done.

<user>116242850924539666934</user><Name>Aaron Anderson<//Name><time>1516398706334</time><Rate>5< /Rate>< text>
I feel it incumbent upon me to share my experience with Ramon's Tire and Auto in Mondota, CA.  On 12/17/2017 I was driving the 5 heading north on a long road trip to Oregon when the flat tire icon appeared on the dash.  It was 5pm when I arrived at the McDonald's with a flat tire.  It was getting dark and it was SUNDAY.  I called 2 other companies who did not answer the phone, but Adrian Gonzalez of Ramon's did.  He assured me that he would likely be able to fix the tire, but that he was 20 minutes away.  To my surprise, he agreed to travel up to the McDonald's to meet me and was able to fix my tire on the spot.  He removed the tire from the vehicle, patched it, and I was back on the road.  When I was up the road a couple exits the light came on again.  I called Adrian.  I don't know this man.  I didn't know him then and I don't know him now.  But he turned around and came directly to help me for a second time!  As it turns out I just needed to drive for a while for the sensor to reset or something, which it did.  It is now January 19th and that tire is still going strong.  Thank you Sir.<//text>

None< /Pics>
< rating>
5</rating>
< text>
Very nice and clean facility.  I was greeted kindly, politely, and with a smile.! The facility is strict on covid procedures, masks, 6 feet apart and it has plenty of hand sanitizer. I was amazed that they had a place for clean ink pens and a place for dirty ink pens.  I was escorted to the back room and given very thorough, and understandable directions by the MRI TECH.  He then came and got me and escorted me to the room for my MRI.  The Tech is very polite, listens to your concerns and accommodates you if you have pain or other issues.  He is also very knowledgeable and takes your care seriously.   I would recommend this facility to all my family and friends.   One thing I was not happy about was there was no headphones with music to listen to. MRI machines are loud even with the earplugs he gives you to wear, take time to put your earplugs in very good. They have handicap access, parking and bathrooms. Do get there early because there is a lengthy history to fill out about your medication, surgeries you have had and dates.  The MRI machine is a capsule type set up that you are sent into so if your clostraphobic get medication to calm you before you go.
Thank you to the Tech and Front office lady for a pleasant procedure< /text>

105617178327971645154<//user_id>

< review>
It was my first experience doing a MRI. I did my best not to move. I understand it is important. A lot of good information can be derived from good scans. It is also important for good communication from the operator. Keeping the patient informed about when it is possible to  adjust position to alleviate discomfort would help expedite the procedure. Hanford Imaging should understand not everyone is claustrophobic, everyone is different and should be treated uniquely so. A small amount of time should be dedicated to getting familiar with whom they are dealing with to insure proper care and consideration is given to each individual. The operator immediately following the end of the session started saying that I was doing excessive amount of moving around. I believe i was not . I felt like  the scans were not of good quality and that he was starting to make excuses for himself. I was unable to have any discussion with him because of his time scheduled. He was starting to prepare for his next customer. If anyone actually reads this comment and is genuinely interested in a intelligent critique i would be available  to speak to a person that is in a supervisor position. Thank you.<//review>

< Text>

<text>I had an extremely pleasant experience at this facility.  I chose at first to go to Fresno Imaging instead of Hanford Imaging do to the reviews on this scroller.  I was not happy with the performance of Fresno Imaging either but thats another review.  Needless to say the day after my appointment with Fresno Imaging I got a call from Hanford Imaging concerned as to why I chose Fresno over Hanford and I explained my concern with the number of poor reviews.  Well to my surprise the issues I had at Fresno imaging were mostly do to poor communication and lack of attention to detail.  Hanford Imaging took care of all of those issues.  They called my insurance and provider and worked out all of the issues for me and called me back with the available appointment times for the very next day.
I went in for my imaging and realized that I had failed to fast properly and had consumed water within the previous 4 hours.   I figured I would have to reschedule for a another day/week but they rearranged their entire schedule around me and scheduled me less than 2 hours later.  Service was absolutely great.
The tech and nurse during my imaging were great.  They explained the process thoroughly as it went along and were very patient during the study's themselves.  During the contrast portion the nurse did an excellent job with a pain free injection and I was done and out less than 5 minutes.
I cannot comment on the image quality at this point but will do so after its reviewed.
I was extremely pleased with my experience and in the event that any future study's are needed I will not hesitate to return.</text><pictures>None</pictures><response>None< /response><gmap_id>0x8094c39b18e1011b:0x3ce7ee1ec93232d6</gmap_id></record>
